translated: Forsling, Sven Oskar, construction engineer, Norrköping, born July 7, 1909 in Järbo, Gävleborg County, son of Oskar F. and Anna Forsling. Married in 1939 to Hanna Hermansson. Children: Sten-Olov b. 1940, Annika b. 1944. Graduated from Katrineholms Technical School in 1934-1936. Worked for building contractor architect Claes Eriksson in Katrineholm from 1936-1937, then worked for Major K.V. Bille in Norrköping from 1937-1938. He became a chief worker for the Building Production Labor Union in Norrköping in 1939. He is a member of the Norrköping city building committee and serves on the boards of the city library and the Folk School. He is also the vice chairman of the Norrköping Social Democratic Party, and chairman of the local chapter of the Swedish Technical Association.
